response.job_title: Enterprise Content Management Specialist at IBM
response.summary:
I'm  a  Systems  engineer  with  emphasis  in  computer  science,  with  over  5  years  of experience  in  the  implementation  of  Enterprise  Content  Management, Case Management and Content Analytics projects using  IBM  Software  tools  and  solutions,  who  likes  to  apply  his  knowledge  in algorithmic  and  programming  to  solve  real  life  problems.

Among  my  strengths  are  the  ease  of  learning  new  things,  the  sense  of responsibility,  teamwork  skills  and  efficiency;  additionally,  I  have  very  good communication  skills in  both  Spanish  and  English. I'm  a  skilled  programmer  in  C++  and  Java,  I  have  a  good  knowledge  of  SQL databases  and  the  main  programming  IDEs  for  application  development. 

Currently,  I  am part  of  the  Software  Lab  Services  team  for  IBM  Colombia,  where  I  work  as  an Enterprise  Content  Management  Software  Specialist  for  the  IBM  Analytics business  unit. In  this  role,  I  have  worked  in  several  software  projects  for  different  industries  in Colombia,  including  Banking,  Oil  and  Gas,  Healthcare  and  Government,  where  I've had  among  my  responsibilities:  requirement  gathering,  installation  and configuration  of  IBM  software  products, architecture design, product enablement, testing and  the  design  and  implementation  of software solutions to  solve  the  customer's needs.
response.skills: Software Development, Java, Programming, C++, Enterprise Content Management, Text Mining, FileNet, Datacap, Case Management, IBM Watson Explorer
